DECLARE
    v_event_date TIMESTAMPTZ;
    v_refund_eligible BOOLEAN;
    v_refund_amount DECIMAL;
    v_result JSONB;
BEGIN
    -- Verify ownership and get event details
    SELECT e.start_date_time, t.ticket_cost
    INTO v_event_date, v_refund_amount
    FROM tickets t
    JOIN contacts c ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
    JOIN event_tickets et ON t.event_ticket_id = et.event_ticket_id
    JOIN events e ON et.event_id = e.event_id
    WHERE t.ticket_id = p_ticket_id
    AND c.email = p_requester_email
    AND t.type = 'issued';
    
    IF NOT FOUND THEN
        RAISE EXCEPTION 'Ticket not found or cannot be cancelled';
    END IF;
    
    -- Check refund eligibility (48 hours before event)
    v_refund_eligible := v_event_date > NOW() + INTERVAL '48 hours';
    
    -- Create cancellation record
    INSERT INTO ticket_cancellations (
        ticket_id,
        cancelled_by_email,
        reason,
        refund_eligible,
        refund_amount,
        cancelled_at
    )
    VALUES (
        p_ticket_id,
        p_requester_email,
        p_reason,
        v_refund_eligible,
        CASE WHEN v_refund_eligible THEN v_refund_amount ELSE 0 END,
        NOW()
    );
    
    -- Update ticket status
    UPDATE tickets
    SET 
        type = 'cancelled'::ticket_type,
        updated_at = NOW()
    WHERE ticket_id = p_ticket_id;
    
    -- Update event ticket availability
    UPDATE event_tickets et
    SET sold = GREATEST(0, COALESCE(sold, 0) - 1)
    FROM tickets t
    WHERE t.ticket_id = p_ticket_id
    AND t.event_ticket_id = et.event_ticket_id;
    
    v_result := jsonb_build_object(
        'ticket_id', p_ticket_id,
        'cancelled_at', NOW(),
        'refund_eligible', v_refund_eligible,
        'refund_amount', CASE WHEN v_refund_eligible THEN v_refund_amount ELSE 0 END,
        'status', 'success'
    );
    
    RETURN v_result;
END;

DECLARE
    v_ticket RECORD;
    v_result JSONB;
BEGIN
    -- Get ticket details
    SELECT 
        t.*,
        c.first_name,
        c.last_name,
        c.email,
        et.name as ticket_type,
        e.name as event_name
    INTO v_ticket
    FROM tickets t
    JOIN contacts c ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
    JOIN event_tickets et ON t.event_ticket_id = et.event_ticket_id
    JOIN events e ON et.event_id = e.event_id
    WHERE t.ticket_id = p_ticket_id;
    
    IF NOT FOUND THEN
        RAISE EXCEPTION 'Ticket not found';
    END IF;
    
    IF v_ticket.type != 'issued' THEN
        RAISE EXCEPTION 'Ticket is not valid for check-in. Status: %', v_ticket.type;
    END IF;
    
    -- Create check-in record
    INSERT INTO check_ins (
        ticket_id,
        checked_in_at,
        checked_in_by
    )
    VALUES (
        p_ticket_id,
        NOW(),
        p_checked_in_by
    )
    ON CONFLICT (ticket_id) DO UPDATE
    SET 
        checked_in_at = NOW(),
        checked_in_by = p_checked_in_by;
    
    v_result := jsonb_build_object(
        'ticket_id', p_ticket_id,
        'attendee_name', v_ticket.first_name || ' ' || v_ticket.last_name,
        'email', v_ticket.email,
        'ticket_type', v_ticket.ticket_type,
        'event_name', v_ticket.event_name,
        'checked_in_at', NOW(),
        'status', 'success'
    );
    
    RETURN v_result;
END;

DECLARE
    v_result JSONB;
    v_ticket_count INTEGER;
    v_email TEXT;
BEGIN
    -- Verify the payment intent matches
    IF NOT EXISTS (
        SELECT 1 FROM registrations 
        WHERE registration_id = p_registration_id 
        AND stripe_payment_intent_id = p_stripe_payment_intent_id
    ) THEN
        RAISE EXCEPTION 'Invalid registration or payment intent';
    END IF;

    -- Update registration status
    UPDATE registrations
    SET 
        payment_status = CASE 
            WHEN p_payment_status = 'succeeded' THEN 'paid'::payment_status
            ELSE 'unpaid'::payment_status
        END,
        updated_at = NOW()
    WHERE registration_id = p_registration_id;

    -- Update tickets status
    UPDATE tickets
    SET 
        type = CASE 
            WHEN p_payment_status = 'succeeded' THEN 'issued'::ticket_type
            ELSE 'cancelled'::ticket_type
        END,
        payment_status = CASE 
            WHEN p_payment_status = 'succeeded' THEN 'paid'::payment_status
            ELSE 'unpaid'::payment_status
        END,
        updated_at = NOW()
    WHERE ticket_id IN (
        SELECT t.ticket_id
        FROM tickets t
        JOIN contacts c ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
        JOIN registrations r ON r.primary_contact_id = c.contact_id
        WHERE r.registration_id = p_registration_id
    );

    -- Get ticket count and email for response
    SELECT 
        COUNT(t.ticket_id),
        c.email
    INTO v_ticket_count, v_email
    FROM tickets t
    JOIN contacts c ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
    JOIN registrations r ON r.primary_contact_id = c.contact_id
    WHERE r.registration_id = p_registration_id
    GROUP BY c.email;

    v_result := jsonb_build_object(
        'registration_id', p_registration_id,
        'payment_status', p_payment_status,
        'tickets_issued', v_ticket_count,
        'email', v_email,
        'status', 'success'
    );

    RETURN v_result;
END;

DECLARE
    v_contact_id UUID;
    v_registration_id UUID;
    v_ticket_id UUID;
    v_ticket JSONB;
BEGIN
    -- Create or update contact
    INSERT INTO contacts (
        email, first_name, last_name, mobile_number,
        type, has_partner, organisation_id
    )
    VALUES (
        p_contact_data->>'email',
        p_contact_data->>'first_name',
        p_contact_data->>'last_name',
        p_contact_data->>'mobile_number',
        (p_contact_data->>'type')::contact_type,
        COALESCE((p_contact_data->>'has_partner')::boolean, false),
        (p_contact_data->>'organisation_id')::uuid
    )
    ON CONFLICT (email) DO UPDATE
    SET 
        first_name = EXCLUDED.first_name,
        last_name = EXCLUDED.last_name,
        mobile_number = EXCLUDED.mobile_number,
        updated_at = NOW()
    RETURNING contact_id INTO v_contact_id;
    
    -- Create registration
    INSERT INTO registrations (
        event_id, primary_contact_id, registration_type,
        registration_data, total_amount
    )
    VALUES (
        p_event_id, v_contact_id, p_registration_data->>'type',
        p_registration_data, (p_registration_data->>'total_amount')::decimal
    )
    RETURNING registration_id INTO v_registration_id;
    
    -- Create tickets
    FOREACH v_ticket IN ARRAY p_tickets
    LOOP
        INSERT INTO tickets (
            event_ticket_id, serial_number, type,
            ticket_cost, ticket_holder_id, claim_code
        )
        VALUES (
            (v_ticket->>'event_ticket_id')::uuid,
            generate_ticket_serial(p_event_id),
            'pending'::ticket_type,
            (v_ticket->>'price')::decimal,
            v_contact_id,
            generate_claim_code()
        );
    END LOOP;
    
    -- Create contact_events association
    INSERT INTO contact_events (contact_id, event_id, registration_id)
    VALUES (v_contact_id, p_event_id, v_registration_id);
    
    RETURN v_registration_id;
END;

DECLARE
    v_registration_id UUID;
    v_contact_id UUID;
    v_attendee JSONB;
    v_ticket JSONB;
    v_ticket_ids UUID[] := '{}';
    v_result JSONB;
BEGIN
    -- Start transaction
    BEGIN
        -- Create or update primary contact
        INSERT INTO contacts (
            email,
            first_name,
            last_name,
            title,
            mobile_number,
            address_line_1,
            address_line_2,
            suburb_city,
            state,
            country,
            postcode,
            type,
            organisation_id
        )
        VALUES (
            p_primary_contact->>'email',
            p_primary_contact->>'first_name',
            p_primary_contact->>'last_name',
            p_primary_contact->>'title',
            p_primary_contact->>'mobile_number',
            p_primary_contact->>'address_line_1',
            p_primary_contact->>'address_line_2',
            p_primary_contact->>'suburb_city',
            p_primary_contact->>'state',
            p_primary_contact->>'country',
            p_primary_contact->>'postcode',
            COALESCE((p_primary_contact->>'type')::contact_type, 'guest'),
            (p_primary_contact->>'organisation_id')::UUID
        )
        ON CONFLICT (email) DO UPDATE
        SET 
            first_name = EXCLUDED.first_name,
            last_name = EXCLUDED.last_name,
            mobile_number = EXCLUDED.mobile_number,
            updated_at = NOW()
        RETURNING contact_id INTO v_contact_id;

        -- Create registration
        INSERT INTO registrations (
            event_id,
            primary_contact_id,
            registration_type,
            registration_data,
            total_amount,
            payment_status,
            stripe_payment_intent_id
        )
        VALUES (
            p_event_id,
            v_contact_id,
            p_registration_type,
            jsonb_build_object(
                'attendees', p_attendees,
                'tickets', p_tickets,
                'primary_contact', p_primary_contact
            ),
            p_total_amount,
            'unpaid',
            p_stripe_payment_intent_id
        )
        RETURNING registration_id INTO v_registration_id;

        -- Process each attendee
        FOREACH v_attendee IN ARRAY p_attendees
        LOOP
            DECLARE
                v_attendee_contact_id UUID;
                v_attendee_tickets JSONB;
                v_single_ticket JSONB;
                v_new_ticket_id UUID;
            BEGIN
                -- Create contact for attendee
                INSERT INTO contacts (
                    email,
                    first_name,
                    last_name,
                    title,
                    mobile_number,
                    type,
                    dietary_requirements,
                    special_needs,
                    has_partner,
                    is_partner,
                    organisation_id
                )
                VALUES (
                    v_attendee->>'email',
                    v_attendee->>'first_name',
                    v_attendee->>'last_name',
                    v_attendee->>'title',
                    v_attendee->>'mobile_number',
                    COALESCE((v_attendee->>'type')::contact_type, 'guest'),
                    v_attendee->>'dietary_requirements',
                    v_attendee->>'special_needs',
                    COALESCE((v_attendee->>'has_partner')::boolean, false),
                    COALESCE((v_attendee->>'is_partner')::boolean, false),
                    (v_attendee->>'organisation_id')::UUID
                )
                ON CONFLICT (email) DO UPDATE
                SET 
                    first_name = EXCLUDED.first_name,
                    last_name = EXCLUDED.last_name,
                    updated_at = NOW()
                RETURNING contact_id INTO v_attendee_contact_id;

                -- Create tickets for this attendee
                v_attendee_tickets := v_attendee->'tickets';
                IF v_attendee_tickets IS NOT NULL THEN
                    FOR v_single_ticket IN SELECT * FROM jsonb_array_elements(v_attendee_tickets)
                    LOOP
                        INSERT INTO tickets (
                            event_ticket_id,
                            serial_number,
                            type,
                            payment_status,
                            ticket_cost,
                            ticket_holder_id,
                            claim_code
                        )
                        VALUES (
                            (v_single_ticket->>'event_ticket_id')::UUID,
                            generate_ticket_serial(p_event_id),
                            'reserved'::ticket_type,
                            'unpaid'::payment_status,
                            (v_single_ticket->>'price')::DECIMAL,
                            v_attendee_contact_id,
                            generate_claim_code()
                        )
                        RETURNING ticket_id INTO v_new_ticket_id;
                        
                        v_ticket_ids := array_append(v_ticket_ids, v_new_ticket_id);
                    END LOOP;
                END IF;
            END;
        END LOOP;

        -- Build result
        v_result := jsonb_build_object(
            'registration_id', v_registration_id,
            'contact_id', v_contact_id,
            'ticket_ids', v_ticket_ids,
            'status', 'success'
        );

        RETURN v_result;
    EXCEPTION
        WHEN OTHERS THEN
            RAISE EXCEPTION 'Registration creation failed: %', SQLERRM;
    END;
END;

BEGIN
    RETURN QUERY
    SELECT 
        t.serial_number,
        c.first_name,
        c.last_name,
        c.email,
        c.mobile_number,
        et.name as ticket_type,
        o.name as organisation_name,
        c.dietary_requirements,
        c.special_needs,
        EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM check_ins ci WHERE ci.ticket_id = t.ticket_id) as checked_in,
        r.registration_type,
        t.payment_status
    FROM tickets t
    JOIN contacts c ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
    JOIN event_tickets et ON t.event_ticket_id = et.event_ticket_id
    LEFT JOIN organisations o ON c.organisation_id = o.organisation_id
    LEFT JOIN registrations r ON r.primary_contact_id = c.contact_id AND r.event_id = p_event_id
    WHERE et.event_id = p_event_id
    AND t.type = 'issued'
    AND (p_filters->>'ticket_type' IS NULL OR et.name = p_filters->>'ticket_type')
    AND (p_filters->>'organisation_id' IS NULL OR c.organisation_id = (p_filters->>'organisation_id')::UUID)
    AND (p_filters->>'checked_in' IS NULL OR 
         (p_filters->>'checked_in' = 'true' AND EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM check_ins ci WHERE ci.ticket_id = t.ticket_id)) OR
         (p_filters->>'checked_in' = 'false' AND NOT EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM check_ins ci WHERE ci.ticket_id = t.ticket_id)))
    ORDER BY c.last_name, c.first_name;
END;

DECLARE
    v_ticket RECORD;
BEGIN
    FOR v_ticket IN
        SELECT t.ticket_id
        FROM tickets t
        JOIN contacts c ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
        WHERE t.type = 'issued'
        AND t.qr_code IS NULL
        AND EXISTS (
            SELECT 1 FROM registrations r
            WHERE r.registration_id = p_registration_id
            AND (r.primary_contact_id = c.contact_id OR 
                 jsonb_path_exists(r.registration_data, '$.attendees[*] ? (@.email == $email)', 
                                   jsonb_build_object('email', c.email)))
        )
    LOOP
        -- Generate QR code data
        PERFORM generate_ticket_qr_data(v_ticket.ticket_id);
    END LOOP;
END;

DECLARE
    v_qr_data JSONB;
    v_qr_string TEXT;
BEGIN
    SELECT jsonb_build_object(
        'ticket_id', t.ticket_id,
        'serial', t.serial_number,
        'event_id', e.event_id,
        'holder', c.first_name || ' ' || c.last_name,
        'type', et.name,
        'valid_from', e.doors_open,
        'valid_until', e.end_date_time
    ) INTO v_qr_data
    FROM tickets t
    JOIN contacts c ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
    JOIN event_tickets et ON t.event_ticket_id = et.event_ticket_id
    JOIN events e ON et.event_id = e.event_id
    WHERE t.ticket_id = p_ticket_id;
    
    -- Create a URL-safe QR string
    v_qr_string := 'https://lodgetix.io/verify/' || 
                   encode(v_qr_data::text::bytea, 'base64');
    
    -- Update ticket with QR code
    UPDATE tickets
    SET qr_code = v_qr_string
    WHERE ticket_id = p_ticket_id;
    
    RETURN v_qr_string;
END;

DECLARE
    v_result JSONB;
BEGIN
    WITH ticket_stats AS (
        SELECT 
            et.event_ticket_id,
            et.name as ticket_type,
            et.price,
            et.max_tickets,
            COALESCE(et.sold, 0) as sold,
            CASE 
                WHEN et.max_tickets IS NULL THEN NULL
                ELSE et.max_tickets - COALESCE(et.sold, 0)
            END as available,
            COUNT(t.ticket_id) FILTER (WHERE t.type = 'issued') as issued,
            COUNT(t.ticket_id) FILTER (WHERE t.type = 'reserved') as reserved,
            COUNT(t.ticket_id) FILTER (WHERE t.payment_status = 'paid') as paid,
            SUM(t.ticket_cost) FILTER (WHERE t.payment_status = 'paid') as revenue
        FROM event_tickets et
        LEFT JOIN tickets t ON et.event_ticket_id = t.event_ticket_id
        WHERE et.event_id = p_event_id
        GROUP BY et.event_ticket_id, et.name, et.price, et.max_tickets, et.sold
    ),
    registration_stats AS (
        SELECT 
            COUNT(DISTINCT r.registration_id) as total_registrations,
            COUNT(DISTINCT r.registration_id) FILTER (WHERE r.payment_status = 'paid') as paid_registrations,
            COUNT(DISTINCT r.registration_id) FILTER (WHERE r.registration_type = 'individual') as individual_registrations,
            COUNT(DISTINCT r.registration_id) FILTER (WHERE r.registration_type = 'lodge') as lodge_registrations,
            COUNT(DISTINCT r.registration_id) FILTER (WHERE r.registration_type = 'delegation') as delegation_registrations,
            SUM(r.total_amount) FILTER (WHERE r.payment_status = 'paid') as total_revenue,
            AVG(r.total_amount) FILTER (WHERE r.payment_status = 'paid') as average_order_value
        FROM registrations r
        WHERE r.event_id = p_event_id
    ),
    attendee_stats AS (
        SELECT 
            COUNT(DISTINCT c.contact_id) as unique_attendees,
            COUNT(DISTINCT c.contact_id) FILTER (WHERE c.type = 'mason') as mason_attendees,
            COUNT(DISTINCT c.contact_id) FILTER (WHERE c.type = 'guest') as guest_attendees,
            COUNT(DISTINCT c.organisation_id) as organisations_represented
        FROM contacts c
        JOIN tickets t ON c.contact_id = t.ticket_holder_id
        JOIN event_tickets et ON t.event_ticket_id = et.event_ticket_id
        WHERE et.event_id = p_event_id AND t.type = 'issued'
    ),
    daily_sales AS (
        SELECT 
            DATE(r.created_at) as sale_date,
            COUNT(*) as registrations,
            SUM(r.total_amount) as revenue
        FROM registrations r
        WHERE r.event_id = p_event_id AND r.payment_status = 'paid'
        GROUP BY DATE(r.created_at)
        ORDER BY sale_date DESC
        LIMIT 30
    )
    SELECT jsonb_build_object(
        'event_id', p_event_id,
        'ticket_stats', (SELECT jsonb_agg(row_to_json(ts.*)) FROM ticket_stats ts),
        'registration_stats', (SELECT row_to_json(rs.*) FROM registration_stats rs),
        'attendee_stats', (SELECT row_to_json(a.*) FROM attendee_stats a),
        'daily_sales', (SELECT jsonb_agg(row_to_json(ds.*)) FROM daily_sales ds),
        'generated_at', NOW()
    ) INTO v_result;
    
    RETURN v_result;
END;

BEGIN
    RETURN QUERY
    SELECT 
        r.registration_id,
        e.name as event_name,
        e.start_date_time as event_date,
        r.registration_type,
        r.total_amount,
        r.payment_status,
        r.created_at as registered_at,
        COUNT(DISTINCT t.ticket_id) as ticket_count,
        e.event_id,
        e.slug as event_slug,
        CASE 
            WHEN e.start_date_time > NOW() AND r.payment_status = 'paid' THEN true
            ELSE false
        END as can_modify
    FROM registrations r
    JOIN contacts c ON r.primary_contact_id = c.contact_id
    JOIN events e ON r.event_id = e.event_id
    LEFT JOIN tickets t ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
    LEFT JOIN event_tickets et ON t.event_ticket_id = et.event_ticket_id AND et.event_id = e.event_id
    WHERE c.email = p_contact_email
    GROUP BY r.registration_id, e.event_id
    ORDER BY e.start_date_time DESC;
END;

BEGIN
    RETURN QUERY
    SELECT 
        t.ticket_id,
        t.serial_number,
        e.name as event_name,
        e.start_date_time as event_date,
        e.location as event_location,
        et.name as ticket_type,
        t.type as ticket_status,
        t.payment_status,
        t.qr_code,
        t.claim_code,
        CASE 
            WHEN t.type = 'issued' AND t.payment_status = 'paid' THEN true
            ELSE false
        END as can_transfer,
        EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM check_ins ci WHERE ci.ticket_id = t.ticket_id) as checked_in,
        e.event_id,
        e.slug as event_slug
    FROM tickets t
    JOIN contacts c ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
    JOIN event_tickets et ON t.event_ticket_id = et.event_ticket_id
    JOIN events e ON et.event_id = e.event_id
    WHERE c.email = p_contact_email
    AND (p_event_id IS NULL OR e.event_id = p_event_id)
    AND t.type IN ('issued', 'reserved', 'pending')
    ORDER BY e.start_date_time DESC, t.created_at DESC;
END;

DECLARE
    v_result JSONB;
BEGIN
    -- Verify access
    IF NOT EXISTS (
        SELECT 1 FROM registrations r
        JOIN contacts c ON r.primary_contact_id = c.contact_id
        WHERE r.registration_id = p_registration_id
        AND c.email = p_requester_email
    ) THEN
        RAISE EXCEPTION 'Registration not found or access denied';
    END IF;
    
    WITH registration_info AS (
        SELECT 
            r.*,
            c.email as primary_email,
            c.first_name as primary_first_name,
            c.last_name as primary_last_name,
            e.name as event_name,
            e.start_date_time as event_date,
            e.location as event_location,
            e.slug as event_slug
        FROM registrations r
        JOIN contacts c ON r.primary_contact_id = c.contact_id
        JOIN events e ON r.event_id = e.event_id
        WHERE r.registration_id = p_registration_id
    ),
    attendee_tickets AS (
        SELECT 
            c.contact_id,
            c.first_name,
            c.last_name,
            c.email,
            c.type as attendee_type,
            c.dietary_requirements,
            c.special_needs,
            jsonb_agg(
                jsonb_build_object(
                    'ticket_id', t.ticket_id,
                    'serial_number', t.serial_number,
                    'ticket_type', et.name,
                    'status', t.type,
                    'checked_in', EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM check_ins ci WHERE ci.ticket_id = t.ticket_id)
                )
            ) as tickets
        FROM registrations r
        JOIN events e ON r.event_id = e.event_id
        JOIN event_tickets et ON et.event_id = e.event_id
        JOIN tickets t ON t.event_ticket_id = et.event_ticket_id
        JOIN contacts c ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
        WHERE r.registration_id = p_registration_id
        GROUP BY c.contact_id
    )
    SELECT jsonb_build_object(
        'registration', row_to_json(ri.*),
        'attendees', jsonb_agg(row_to_json(at.*))
    ) INTO v_result
    FROM registration_info ri, attendee_tickets at
    GROUP BY ri.*;
    
    RETURN v_result;
END;

DECLARE
    v_result JSONB;
BEGIN
    WITH registration_info AS (
        SELECT 
            r.registration_id,
            r.registration_type,
            r.total_amount,
            r.payment_status,
            r.created_at,
            c.contact_id as primary_contact_id,
            c.email as primary_email,
            c.first_name as primary_first_name,
            c.last_name as primary_last_name,
            c.mobile_number as primary_phone,
            e.event_id,
            e.name as event_name,
            e.start_date_time as event_date,
            e.doors_open,
            e.location as event_location,
            e.dress_code,
            e.important_information,
            e.slug as event_slug,
            -- Generate registration number
            'REG-' || UPPER(SUBSTRING(r.registration_id::TEXT, 1, 8)) as registration_number
        FROM registrations r
        JOIN contacts c ON r.primary_contact_id = c.contact_id
        JOIN events e ON r.event_id = e.event_id
        WHERE r.registration_id = p_registration_id
    ),
    ticket_details AS (
        SELECT 
            t.ticket_id,
            t.serial_number,
            t.qr_code,
            t.claim_code,
            et.name as ticket_type,
            c.first_name || ' ' || c.last_name as attendee_name,
            c.email as attendee_email,
            c.dietary_requirements,
            c.special_needs
        FROM tickets t
        JOIN contacts c ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
        JOIN event_tickets et ON t.event_ticket_id = et.event_ticket_id
        JOIN registration_info ri ON et.event_id = ri.event_id
        WHERE t.type = 'issued'
        AND t.payment_status = 'paid'
        AND EXISTS (
            SELECT 1 FROM registrations r
            WHERE r.registration_id = p_registration_id
            AND (r.primary_contact_id = c.contact_id OR 
                 jsonb_path_exists(r.registration_data, '$.attendees[*] ? (@.email == $email)', 
                                   jsonb_build_object('email', c.email)))
        )
    )
    SELECT jsonb_build_object(
        'registration_id', ri.registration_id,
        'registration_number', ri.registration_number,
        'registration_type', ri.registration_type,
        'total_amount', ri.total_amount,
        'primary_contact_id', ri.primary_contact_id,
        'primary_email', ri.primary_email,
        'primary_first_name', ri.primary_first_name,
        'primary_last_name', ri.primary_last_name,
        'primary_phone', ri.primary_phone,
        'event_id', ri.event_id,
        'event_name', ri.event_name,
        'event_date', ri.event_date,
        'doors_open', ri.doors_open,
        'event_location', ri.event_location,
        'event_slug', ri.event_slug,
        'dress_code', ri.dress_code,
        'important_information', ri.important_information,
        'tickets', COALESCE(
            (SELECT jsonb_agg(row_to_json(td.*)) FROM ticket_details td),
            '[]'::jsonb
        )
    ) INTO v_result
    FROM registration_info ri;
    
    RETURN v_result;
END;

DECLARE
    v_ticket RECORD;
BEGIN
    -- Get all tickets for this registration
    FOR v_ticket IN
        SELECT DISTINCT et.event_ticket_id, COUNT(*) as ticket_count
        FROM tickets t
        JOIN event_tickets et ON t.event_ticket_id = et.event_ticket_id
        JOIN contacts c ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
        JOIN registrations r ON r.primary_contact_id = c.contact_id
        WHERE r.registration_id = p_registration_id
        AND t.type = 'reserved'
        GROUP BY et.event_ticket_id
    LOOP
        -- Decrease sold count
        UPDATE event_tickets
        SET sold = GREATEST(0, COALESCE(sold, 0) - v_ticket.ticket_count)
        WHERE event_ticket_id = v_ticket.event_ticket_id;
    END LOOP;
    
    -- Delete the reserved tickets
    DELETE FROM tickets
    WHERE ticket_id IN (
        SELECT t.ticket_id
        FROM tickets t
        JOIN contacts c ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
        JOIN registrations r ON r.primary_contact_id = c.contact_id
        WHERE r.registration_id = p_registration_id
        AND t.type = 'reserved'
    );
END;

DECLARE
    v_draft_id UUID;
BEGIN
    INSERT INTO registration_drafts (
        event_id,
        email,
        draft_data,
        expires_at
    )
    VALUES (
        p_event_id,
        p_email,
        p_draft_data,
        NOW() + INTERVAL '7 days'
    )
    ON CONFLICT (event_id, email) DO UPDATE
    SET 
        draft_data = EXCLUDED.draft_data,
        updated_at = NOW(),
        expires_at = EXCLUDED.expires_at
    RETURNING draft_id INTO v_draft_id;
    
    RETURN v_draft_id;
END;

DECLARE
    v_event RECORD;
    v_registration RECORD;
BEGIN
    -- Find events happening in the next 48 hours that haven't had reminders sent
    FOR v_event IN
        SELECT e.event_id, e.name, e.start_date_time
        FROM events e
        WHERE e.status = 'published'
        AND e.start_date_time > NOW()
        AND e.start_date_time <= NOW() + INTERVAL '48 hours'
        AND NOT EXISTS (
            SELECT 1 FROM email_logs el
            WHERE el.email_type = 'reminder'
            AND el.created_at > NOW() - INTERVAL '24 hours'
            AND el.registration_id IN (
                SELECT registration_id FROM registrations WHERE event_id = e.event_id
            )
        )
    LOOP
        -- Queue reminder emails for all confirmed registrations
        FOR v_registration IN
            SELECT r.registration_id, c.email
            FROM registrations r
            JOIN contacts c ON r.primary_contact_id = c.contact_id
            WHERE r.event_id = v_event.event_id
            AND r.payment_status = 'paid'
        LOOP
            -- Insert into email queue (to be processed by edge function)
            INSERT INTO email_queue (
                registration_id,
                email_type,
                scheduled_for,
                status
            ) VALUES (
                v_registration.registration_id,
                'reminder',
                NOW(),
                'pending'
            );
        END LOOP;
    END LOOP;
END;

DECLARE
    v_new_holder_id UUID;
    v_old_holder_id UUID;
    v_result JSONB;
BEGIN
    -- Get current holder
    SELECT ticket_holder_id INTO v_old_holder_id
    FROM tickets
    WHERE ticket_id = p_ticket_id;
    
    IF NOT FOUND THEN
        RAISE EXCEPTION 'Ticket not found';
    END IF;
    
    -- Create or update new holder
    INSERT INTO contacts (
        email,
        first_name,
        last_name,
        mobile_number,
        type,
        dietary_requirements,
        special_needs
    )
    VALUES (
        p_new_holder_email,
        p_new_holder_data->>'first_name',
        p_new_holder_data->>'last_name',
        p_new_holder_data->>'mobile_number',
        COALESCE((p_new_holder_data->>'type')::contact_type, 'guest'),
        p_new_holder_data->>'dietary_requirements',
        p_new_holder_data->>'special_needs'
    )
    ON CONFLICT (email) DO UPDATE
    SET 
        first_name = COALESCE(EXCLUDED.first_name, contacts.first_name),
        last_name = COALESCE(EXCLUDED.last_name, contacts.last_name),
        updated_at = NOW()
    RETURNING contact_id INTO v_new_holder_id;
    
    -- Create transfer record
    INSERT INTO ticket_transfers (
        ticket_id,
        from_contact_id,
        to_contact_id,
        transferred_by,
        transferred_at
    )
    VALUES (
        p_ticket_id,
        v_old_holder_id,
        v_new_holder_id,
        p_transferred_by,
        NOW()
    );
    
    -- Update ticket holder
    UPDATE tickets
    SET 
        ticket_holder_id = v_new_holder_id,
        updated_at = NOW()
    WHERE ticket_id = p_ticket_id;
    
    v_result := jsonb_build_object(
        'ticket_id', p_ticket_id,
        'new_holder_id', v_new_holder_id,
        'transferred_at', NOW(),
        'status', 'success'
    );
    
    RETURN v_result;
END;

DECLARE
    v_ticket RECORD;
    v_result JSONB;
BEGIN
    IF p_verification_type = 'qr' THEN
        SELECT 
            t.*,
            c.first_name,
            c.last_name,
            c.email,
            et.name as ticket_type,
            e.name as event_name,
            e.start_date_time,
            e.end_date_time
        INTO v_ticket
        FROM tickets t
        JOIN contacts c ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
        JOIN event_tickets et ON t.event_ticket_id = et.event_ticket_id
        JOIN events e ON et.event_id = e.event_id
        WHERE t.qr_code = p_verification_code;
    ELSE
        SELECT 
            t.*,
            c.first_name,
            c.last_name,
            c.email,
            et.name as ticket_type,
            e.name as event_name,
            e.start_date_time,
            e.end_date_time
        INTO v_ticket
        FROM tickets t
        JOIN contacts c ON t.ticket_holder_id = c.contact_id
        JOIN event_tickets et ON t.event_ticket_id = et.event_ticket_id
        JOIN events e ON et.event_id = e.event_id
        WHERE t.claim_code = UPPER(p_verification_code);
    END IF;
    
    IF NOT FOUND THEN
        RETURN jsonb_build_object(
            'valid', false,
            'error', 'Ticket not found',
            'status', 'error'
        );
    END IF;
    
    -- Check ticket validity
    IF v_ticket.type != 'issued' THEN
        RETURN jsonb_build_object(
            'valid', false,
            'error', 'Ticket is ' || v_ticket.type,
            'status', 'error'
        );
    END IF;
    
    -- Check if already checked in
    IF EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM check_ins WHERE ticket_id = v_ticket.ticket_id) THEN
        RETURN jsonb_build_object(
            'valid', false,
            'error', 'Ticket already checked in',
            'status', 'error'
        );
    END IF;
    
    -- Check event timing
    IF NOW() < v_ticket.start_date_time - INTERVAL '4 hours' THEN
        RETURN jsonb_build_object(
            'valid', false,
            'error', 'Event has not started yet',
            'status', 'error'
        );
    END IF;
    
    IF NOW() > v_ticket.end_date_time THEN
        RETURN jsonb_build_object(
            'valid', false,
            'error', 'Event has ended',
            'status', 'error'
        );
    END IF;
    
    v_result := jsonb_build_object(
        'valid', true,
        'ticket_id', v_ticket.ticket_id,
        'attendee_name', v_ticket.first_name || ' ' || v_ticket.last_name,
        'email', v_ticket.email,
        'ticket_type', v_ticket.ticket_type,
        'event_name', v_ticket.event_name,
        'serial_number', v_ticket.serial_number,
        'status', 'success'
    );
    
    RETURN v_result;
END;

    pg_stat_statements.blk_read_time,
    pg_stat_statements.blk_write_time,
    pg_stat_statements.temp_blk_read_time,
    pg_stat_statements.temp_blk_write_time,
    pg_stat_statements.wal_records,

    pg_stat_statements.jit_inlining_time,
    pg_stat_statements.jit_optimization_count,
    pg_stat_statements.jit_optimization_time,
    pg_stat_statements.jit_emission_count,
    pg_stat_statements.jit_emission_time
   FROM pg_stat_statements(true) pg_stat_statements(userid, dbid, toplevel, queryid, query, plans, total_plan_time, min_plan_time, max_plan_time, mean_plan_time, stddev_plan_time, calls, total_exec_time, min_exec_time, max_exec_time, mean_exec_time, stddev_exec_time, rows, shared_blks_hit, shared_blks_read, shared_blks_dirtied, shared_blks_written, local_blks_hit, local_blks_read, local_blks_dirtied, local_blks_written, temp_blks_read, temp_blks_written, blk_read_time, blk_write_time, temp_blk_read_time, temp_blk_write_time, wal_records, wal_fpi, wal_bytes, jit_functions, jit_generation_time, jit_inlining_count, jit_inlining_time, jit_optimization_count, jit_optimization_time, jit_emission_count, jit_emission_time);

SELECT c.contact_id,
    c.email,
    c.first_name,
    c.last_name,
    count(DISTINCT t.ticket_id) AS total_tickets,
    count(DISTINCT e.event_id) AS events_registered,
    count(DISTINCT
        CASE
            WHEN (t.type = 'issued'::ticket_type) THEN t.ticket_id
            ELSE NULL::uuid
        END) AS issued_tickets
   FROM (((contacts c
     LEFT JOIN tickets t ON ((c.contact_id = t.ticket_holder_id)))
     LEFT JOIN event_tickets et ON ((t.event_ticket_id = et.event_ticket_id)))
     LEFT JOIN events e ON ((et.event_id = e.event_id)))
  GROUP BY c.contact_id;

SELECT e.event_id,
    e.name,
    e.slug,
    e.start_date_time,
    e.status,
    e.total_capacity,
    count(DISTINCT et.event_ticket_id) AS ticket_types,
    sum(et.sold) AS total_sold,
    sum(et.available) AS total_available,
    count(DISTINCT r.registration_id) AS total_registrations
   FROM ((events e
     LEFT JOIN event_tickets et ON ((e.event_id = et.event_id)))
     LEFT JOIN registrations r ON ((e.event_id = r.event_id)))
  GROUP BY e.event_id;
